ğŸŒŸ Containers have become the de facto way to package and deploy applications in the cloud. They offer a number of advantages over traditional virtual machines, including faster startup times, greater efficiency, and the ability to scale horizontally. However, containers also introduce new security challenges.

ğŸŒŸ Container security is the practice of protecting containers from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, disruption, modification, or destruction. It involves implementing a variety of security measures at different stages of the container lifecycle, from development to deployment to production.

Here are some best practices for container security:

